<br>
The PC version lacks the unlockable multiplayer dojo mode that the console versions have, which isn't internet playable anyway. (as gleaned from the IGN head-to-head comparison, they chose the XBox version as being the best). <br>
<br>
Actually, from what I've read and been told by my friend who bought the game, the PC version is...lacking polish. On the upside, they can actually patch that version (and the XBox one, technically).<br>
<br>
There is a massively multiplayer game in the works called (at this point anyway) The Matrix Online...however, it's at least a year off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slovodraw01>Slovodraw01</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/7/03 10:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pub6.picturehost.co.uk/eightydbuddyicon2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enter the matrix</span><hr size=1> the game in my opinion is not that good. Im thinking that they rushed it to finish with the movie. Which is getting on my nerves. Its fun but it just seems kinda klunky. In the end in kinda regret preordering it. But i bought it for xbox so i dont know how the pc version is. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://pub5.picturehost.co.uk/banner1b.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/totdeer" target="top">Tot Deer Studios</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=snowthefox>Snow the Fox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/snowthefox/ring.txt" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/15/03 5:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/snowthefox/avatar-ryu.txt HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enter the matrix</span><hr size=1> It's a game based on a blockbuster movie franchise, what more could you expect.<br>
I can't think of one game like that that has been good.<br>
I'm sure there's a few maybe. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/snowthefox/airship.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=themightyservo>The Mighty Servo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/15/03 6:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://filebox.vt.edu/users/cmayer/images/servo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enter the matrix</span><hr size=1> Jurassic Park for Genesis and SNES (different games though), X-Wing, Tie Fighter, Dark Forces and the sequels...actually, probably 3/4 of the Star Wars games are good to great, Alien fps games, Alien vs. Predator games, some good Terminator fps games years ago, True Lies for SNES, Disney's Aladdin and Lion King games (SNES and Genesis), many Star Trek games (old and new), Dune games (especially Dune II...forerunner to Command and Conquer and basically the whole rts genre), and more that I can't think of off the top of my head.<br>
<br>
True many movie and TV games are crummy...but there have been a significant number of good ones too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=snowthefox>Snow the Fox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/snowthefox/ring.txt" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/15/03 3:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/snowthefox/avatar-ryu.txt HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enter the matrix</span><hr size=1> I'd have to disagree about quite a few of those titles.<br>
<br>
But yeah, I wasn't saying every game based on a movie sucked, most of the Star Wars games are good.  X-Wing wasn't great like TIE Fighter though.. I wouldn't compare them.<br>
AvP 2 was a flop in my opinion, but the first AvP rocked my socks.<br>
Star Trek games just plain suck, I haven't seen one good one other than Elite Force ( the Voyager one ).<br>
Dune was probably the monumental movie to VG game.<br>
Aladdin and Lion King aren't what I'd call great games though they were somewhat fun.<br>
I'unno any good Terminator games.  Time Crisis games aren't my bag though so it's probably just me.<br>
Never played True Lies, but it sounds like a Lion King/ Aladdin thing. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/snowthefox/airship.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=themightyservo>The Mighty Servo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/15/03 4:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=671.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://filebox.vt.edu/users/cmayer/images/servo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enter the matrix</span><hr size=1> X-Wing was great for it's time. I agree, not *as* good as Tie Fighter...but it did precede it by a few years. Some of the shortcomings were addressed in the Mac version and then the Collector's edition (garoud shaded graphics, yay!). Still, fondly remembered because of what it was to other games at release time.  <br>
<br>
I never got into either AvP game myself, I'm thinking more along the lines of reviews...both were accepted as good games...as opposed to many other TV/movie games.<br>
<br>
Star Trek had several adventure style games and such in the early/mid nineties that were good. (Final Unity for one). I haven't played many of them recently either...but I do remember most of the early ones doing quite well.<br>
<br>
Aladdin (and the Lion King) games were also recieved as solid games when released. Personally I still enjoy the Genesis Aladdin, helmed by a pre-Shiny Dave Perry. I suppose if you don't like the 2D Earthworm Jim games and stuff, you wouldn't like that one either...but I do.<br>
<br>
For Terminator I'm thinking more along the lines of Terminator: Future Shock and such...not the arcade game (though that was a decent game for that style). <br>
<br>
True Lies was, I believe, similar to the Jurassic Park SNES game and Metal Gear in a way...never was able to get my hands on that one though. It was also received well at the time, and my gamer friends that did play it say it was good.<br>
<br>
No disagreeing that *most* games based on movies and TV series blow big time. Even then, the ratio of good to bad is probably better than game to screen conversions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I'm definitely wary of the quality for translations between film and game in either direction.<br>
